sentences.en: AIM : To set up the HPLC fingerprint of Anemarrhena asphodeloides.
sentences.cn: 目的: 建立知母高效液相色谱指纹图谱.

sentences.en: But in actual fact there are ways to fool those fingerprint scanners.
sentences.cn: 但事实上,有很多方法可以骗过这个指纹扫描仪.

sentences.en: He took her to jail, where she was fingerprinted and booked.
sentences.cn: 他将她带到监狱，她在那里被提取了指纹并登记在册。

sentences.en: He was careful not to leave any fingerprints .
His fingerprints were all over the gun.
Let's fingerprint the canoe, see if we come up with anything.
sentences.cn: 让我们提取一下独木舟上的指纹，看看能不能有什么发现。

sentences.en: Maynard has personally experienced many fingerprint - related snafus, often related to employment.
sentences.cn: 梅纳德自己经历了数次与指纹相关的麻烦, 通常是因为求职.

sentences.en: Objective : To study the fingerprint of Radix Salviae Miltiorrhizae of Xiangdan Injection.
sentences.cn: 目的: 研究香丹注射剂、原药材的指纹图谱.

sentences.en: Objective : To study the ultramicro Rhizoma Cyperi and establish its fingerprint.
sentences.cn: 目的: 研究香附超微饮片的气相色谱指纹图谱,为科学评价及有效控制其质量提供可靠方法.

sentences.en: Objective To create a multi - digital sensor and living fingerprint capture system.
sentences.cn: 目的创立一种警用多个数字传感器同通道活体指纹采集系统.

sentences.en: So fingerprint identification has been applied formally in biologic character identification technology.
sentences.cn: 这个特点使得指纹在生物特征识别技术中得以正式应用.

sentences.en: Sunshellone's fingerprint, is like magnolia blossoms in the End of the World.
sentences.cn: 阳光的指纹, 好似木兰花,开在海角.

sentences.en: That makes fingerprint lock away from any interruption of static.
sentences.cn: 这使得指纹锁定远离任何中断静.

sentences.en: The aircraft has equipment to fingerprint enemy planes.
sentences.cn: 这架飞机有辨别敌机的装置.

sentences.en: The author's fingerprint is quite obvious in all of his works.
sentences.cn: 作者的特色在他所有的作品中都很明显.

sentences.en: The court heard evidence from a fingerprint expert.
sentences.cn: 法院听取了指纹专家的证词.

sentences.en: The fingerprint expert was asked to testify at the trial.
sentences.cn: 指纹专家应邀出庭作证.

sentences.en: The police questioned Beresford and took his fingerprints (= made a record of them ) .
sentences.cn: 警察审问了贝雷斯福德，并提取了他的指纹。

sentences.en: The technology of fingerprint identification is a kind of mature biological technology.
sentences.cn: 指纹识别技术是一种比较成熟的生物技术.

指纹技术；指纹法（蛋白质分析）

trans.tran_en: a mark made by the pattern of lines at the end of a person’s finger, which is used by the police to find out who has committed a crime
If someone is fingerprinted, the police take their fingerprints
